SAN FRANCISCO
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
SAN FRANCISCO - the city on the bay, is a favorite of everyone. From Grant Avenue, in the heart of
Chinatown, with its Festivals, to Nob Hill, Fisherman's Wharf or the Golden Gate Bridge, there is so
much to see. The quaint Cable Cars and other historical attractions blend with fine restaurants,
elegant stores, and famous hotels such as Inter-Continental's renowned Mark Hopkins, to create a
unique atmosphere. Pan Am serves San Francisco every day from New York, Houston, Miami,
Central and South America, Hawaii, Tokyo, Hong Kong, and London. In fact, you can get to
San Francisco on Pan Am from just about any place in the world.
